    "long_instructions": "### Alternating Patterns with Nested Loops\r\n\r\nUse nested loops to switch between different parts of your code, allowing you to tweak one loop while the other plays.\r\n\r\n**Do This**:\r\n- Create a loop that repeats 3 times, layering a drum, bass, and lead part using play together.\r\n- Create a second loop that also repeats 3 times with a different set of drum, bass, and lead layers.\r\n- Nest both loops inside another loop that plays 3 times (see image below for reference).\r\n- Press \"Run\" – while one loop plays, the other is silent. Use that time to edit and experiment!\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/71c0ad8e20a2a083deeab43651f60787-image-1742403105866.51.43 AM.png)",
